# Frontend (Nuxt 4)

## i18n

- All UI strings in `i18n/locales/en.json` and `i18n/locales/de.json` — never hardcode copy in `.vue` files
- Use `t('key')` or `$t('key')`; SEO meta via `seo.*` keys
- German copy: informal "du", professional but approachable

## Routing

- Default locale `en`; German at `/de/...` (`prefix_except_default`)
- Internal links: `localePath('/blog')`, not raw paths
- Content queries: `useLocalizedContentPath()` — EN `/blog`, DE `/de/blog`

## Components

- shadcn-vue: `app/components/ui/` — import `@/components/ui/...`
- Layout: `app/components/layout/` with `pathPrefix: false` (use `<AppHeader>`, not `<LayoutAppHeader>`)
- Toasts: `toast` from `vue-sonner`; `<Toaster />` in layout (shadcn wrapper)

## Theme

- localStorage key: `werkscode-theme`
- Dark mode via `document.documentElement.classList.toggle('dark', ...)`

## Page patterns

```vue
const { t } = useI18n()
const localePath = useLocalePath()
const { localizedPath } = useLocalizedContentPath()

useSeoMeta({
  title: () => t('seo.blog.title'),
  description: () => t('seo.blog.description'),
})
```
